<div class="row">
  <div class="panel"><h1>Welcome to the EMC VNX VDI Calculator*</h1>
  <p>*Not official sanctioned by EMC, I did this in my spare time. If you have questions please send me a message <a href="http://twitter.com/jon_2vcps">@jon_2vcps</a>. The <a href="https://github.com/2vcps/vdi-calc">source is on github</a> Please Fork me! 

<p>This calculator attempts to estimate the EMC storage needed for VMware View, Citrix PVS and MCS environments. It is based on the math
from this <a href=http://www.emc.com/collateral/software/white-papers/h11096-vdi-sizing-wp.pdf>whitepaper.</a> 
Remember this is just an estimation and real world experience can never be replaced. Use the as a guide in order to get started.
<br>
<h1>Enter Your VDI Sizing Information</h1>
<form method="get" action="/calc_home">
VDI Type:<select name="vditype">
  <option value="VMWare View">VMware View</option>
  <option value="Citrix PVS">Citrix PVS</option>
  <option value="Citrix MCS">Citrix MCS</option>
</select><br /> 
Number of Desktops <input type="text" name="nDesktops"><br/>
Steady State IOPS <input type="text" name="ioSteady"><br/>
Average Ram per Desktop(amount of RAM in GB per Desktop) <input type="text" name="avgRam"><br/>
Concurrent User Percent (between 1-100) - percentage of users that are on at once. <input type="text" name="conCurr"><br/>
Max size in GB of Linked Clones/Write Cache Files <input type="number" name="maxLC"><br/>
Memory Reservation Percentage (If you don't know put 50) - How much memory reservation you will use per desktop. <input type="number" name="memRes"><br/>
Storage Protocol <select name="storProto">
	<option value="NFS">NFS</option>
	<option value="FC">Fiber Channel</option>
	</select><br/>
<br>User data per user(GB) <input type="number" name="userData"><br/>
Additional Application Storage GB - non-vdi related disks for VM's <input type="number" name="addStor"><br/>
Number of Base Images <input type="number" name="baseImg"><br/>
<input type="submit" value="Go">
</form>
</div>
